olive oil
½ tin Pineapple Slices
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
20 g butter
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet Crushed Peanuts

• Reserve pineapple juice, then drain pineapple slices (see ingredients).
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook pineapple slices until lightly charred, 2-3 minutes each side. Roughly chop and set aside.

• Cut chicken thigh into 2cm chunks. Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 4-5 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add mild Caribbean jerk seasoning, tossing chicken to coat. Add reserved pineapple juice (2 tbs for 2 people / 1/4 cup for 4 people) and the butter and cook until chicken is sticky, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• In a large bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, baby leaves, mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Top tortillas with slaw, Caribbean chicken and pineapple.
• Sprinkle with crushed peanuts and shredded Cheddar cheese to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling over the peanuts!